Class Worker

Runnable
public class Worker
extends Bee
The female worker bee has the task of going to the flower field and collecting their assigned resource - nectar or pollen. A worker will always get exactly 1 unit of their resource each time they go out to the field and when they return will deposit that resource into the bee hive. After each successful gather, the worker will try again to gather, as long as the beehive is active.

  • Method Details

    • toString

      public String toString()
      The worker bee returns a string that contains the role, followed by Bee.toString()'s string, e.g.:
      {RESOURCE} ROLE #{id}


      Here, {RESOURCE} is the resource, e.g. NECTAR or POLLEN, ROLE is the role (should always be WORKER, but let the superclass toString() figure that out), and {id} is the unique id.
      Overrides:
      toString in class Bee
      Returns:
      the string as described here

    • run

      public void run()
      When the worker runs, they will enter the field. If there is a free flower, they will sleep the required time to simulate the extraction, then they will leave the field and deposit their resource into the bee hive. This process repeats until the bee hive becomes inactive.
      Specified by:
      run in interface Runnable
      Overrides:
      run in class Thread
